				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1918720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204708" alt="Scorpion451" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1918720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;" >Scorpion451</a></span> <span class="odate time_1471284225 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Aug 2016 18:03</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2564269">
									

<p>Excellent essay, spot-on advice here.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;One&nbsp;additional&nbsp;observation/suggestion&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;'Clinical&nbsp;≠&nbsp;Verbose'&nbsp;section</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;One&nbsp;additional&nbsp;observation/suggestion&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;'Clinical&nbsp;≠&nbsp;Verbose'&nbsp;section:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Word choice is also about eliminating ambiguity while saying things indirectly. As Mark Twain put it, &quot;<em>The difference between the right word and</em> almost <em>the right word is the difference between 'lightning' and 'lightning bug'.</em>&quot;</p>
<p>For instance, saying that the gas &quot;makes people immortal&quot; doesn't describe the full range of effects, and actually provides some false information, because that's not <em>really</em> what this does.</p>
<p>The phrase &quot;animal cells&quot; instead of &quot;people&quot; or &quot;organisms&quot; tells us that the effect isn't limited to humans, and doesn't affect an organism as a whole- only the cells. The individual pieces of an organism are simply &quot;unable to cease life function&quot;, no matter their current state. Effects pointedly not listed: &quot;enhanced regeneration&quot;, &quot;ability to function effectively despite massive trauma&quot;, &quot;pain resistance&quot;, and &quot;immunity to infection&quot;.</p>
<p>By picking just the right words to say what he wanted, Kalinin describes a multilayered and disturbing effect, without directly describing the vast majority of its effects at all.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
