														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2564284">
									

<p>Like anything else, you're never going to please everybody- The key is that your audience as a whole is able to understand the idea well enough for it to work. 2323 does that, hence all the upvotes.</p>
<p>Its a thing in visual art, too- Dada aside, the goal is always to have an image be comprehensible at a glance (even abstract works aim to convey a general emotion or impact upon initial viewing). It's one thing to have to explain why there's a giant bird building a nest on a building- its another if you have to explain to everyone that the picture <em>is</em> a giant bird building a nest on a building.</p>

