														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2564334">
									

<blockquote>
<p>&quot;high-pitched whimpering gasps&quot; is one trait with one adjective and one adverb.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is it? &quot;Whimpering&quot; is an active participle, and thus an adjective. &quot;Pitched&quot; is a passive participle, and thus another adjective, in this case modified by a third adjective.</p>
<p>Your principle that one trait is allowed only one adjective is a reasonable guideline, but this example shows it's not an absolute rule.</p>

							</div>

								
					
